{
  "texts": [
    "A possible remedy is to use the Wasserstein distance in the cost function [637].",
    "Additionally, GANs can be modified to include inputs that control the generated data.",
    "This can be achieved in a supervised manner with conditional GANs [638].",
    "The conditional GAN does not just receive random noise, but also an additional input.",
    "This supplementary input is considered by the discriminator, which assesses whether the input-output pairs are real or generated."
  ]
}